==English==

===Alternative spellings===
* [[laughing stock]]

===Etymology===
* [[laughing]] + [[stock]]. Thought to originate from the time when stocks were used to punish and humiliate petty criminals.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{idiomatic}} An object of [[ridicule]], someone who is publicly [[ridicule]]d; a butt of [[sport]]. - Shakespeare
#: '''Quotations'''
#: ''When he talked, he talked nonsense, and made himself the '''laughingstock''' of his hearers.'' - [[Macaulay]]
#: ''After I got drunk and fell asleep naked outside my manager's house, I've been the '''laughingstock''' of the club.''
